# Logs
# Anchored to root — the unanchored `logs` rule was silently matching
# every nested `logs/` directory, including `src/v3/editors/logs/`
# (which holds the in-app Logs panel — see LogsEditor.jsx). Caught
# 2026-05-02 when verifying Phase 3 lift-summary logging.
/logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

backups
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# Environment
.env
.env.*

# OS
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Reference materials (proprietary Live2D assets)
reference/

# Live2D export session prompts (development artifacts, not user-facing)
docs/archive/sessions/

# Claude Code local state
.claude/

# Project files (binary, large)
*.psd
*.stretch
*.cmo3
__pycache__/

# Local dev scripts (platform-specific)
_start.bat

# Export artifacts (SS dev testing output, not source)
*.rig.log.json
*_live2d*.zip
girl.png
waifu.png
shelby*.png
shelby*.can3
*.can3
*.blend
*.blend1

# Cubism Editor "Export For Runtime" output — generated, not source.
# Catches the model_live2d/ directory pattern + bare runtime files.
*.moc3
*.model3.json
*.cdi3.json
*.physics3.json
*.motion3.json
*.exp3.json
*.userdata3.json
*.2048
*.4096
model_live2d/
*_live2d/

# Local test export folders (user-side scratch space, not source)
New Folder/
New Folder_*/
*_runtime/

# Reference media — videos / extracted frames / stray downloads (too large,
# often proprietary Hiyori/commercial Live2D samples).
*.mp4
*.jfif
frames/
frames */
